1
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:41,240
♪In rain or shine♪

2
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:46,870
♪When you're around,
the sun shines through♪

3
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Spare ourselves the endless thoughts
and guessing games♪

4
00:00:52,930 --> 00:00:58,880
♪Let's just meet
and escape these frames♪

5
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:02,600
♪I stand within the shadows deep♪

6
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:08,030
♪My hand outstretched,
your rescue I keep♪

7
00:01:08,220 --> 00:01:12,850
♪Even if the world falls apart♪

8
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:15,870
♪No distance is too far♪

9
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:21,390
♪To stop us from coming together♪

10
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:27,710
♪Through the night,
you're at the end of the line♪

11
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:32,730
♪To protect you is my humble wish♪

12
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:36,920
♪Farewell, to the timid soul I knew♪

13
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:42,550
♪It was you who made me brave and new♪

14
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:46,180
=Always Home=
(Adapted from Xiao Ge's novel, Always Home)

15
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:49,180
=Episode 12=
(Even the Ace Student Can't Solve ABC)

16
00:01:53,830 --> 00:01:54,630
Eat up.

17
00:01:56,420 --> 00:01:56,990
Come.

18
00:02:02,140 --> 00:02:02,780
Chen Huan'er.

19
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:05,990
Thanks to your sharp sense of smell.

20
00:02:06,270 --> 00:02:07,390
I was so scared.

21
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:09,020
It's the first time I've seen

22
00:02:09,020 --> 00:02:10,230
Aunt Hao looking like this.

23
00:02:10,260 --> 00:02:12,120
As someone
who has been through it before,

24
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:14,070
I can understand Aunt Hao's

25
00:02:14,070 --> 00:02:15,110
current mood.

26
00:02:15,620 --> 00:02:16,620
Aunt Hao

27
00:02:16,700 --> 00:02:18,740
just needs some time to accept it.

28
00:02:21,580 --> 00:02:23,550
Song Cong seems to be pretty blue, too.

29
00:02:23,990 --> 00:02:25,300
He sent me a message saying

30
00:02:25,420 --> 00:02:26,820
he bought an induction cooker

31
00:02:26,860 --> 00:02:28,700
and even set up a small table
for his mother.

32
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:32,790
Won't your Aunt Hao
feel even worse that way?

33
00:02:34,230 --> 00:02:35,230
Why so, Mom?

34
00:02:35,510 --> 00:02:36,420
Think about it.

35
00:02:36,580 --> 00:02:38,900
Your Aunt Hao was such a capable person.

36
00:02:39,020 --> 00:02:40,740
Everything in the house depended on her.

37
00:02:41,270 --> 00:02:42,830
Song Cong wants to be filial.

38
00:02:43,140 --> 00:02:45,620
But by doing so, he reminded Aunt Hao

39
00:02:45,860 --> 00:02:47,270
how she had become a burden to them.

40
00:02:49,180 --> 00:02:50,230
What should we do then?

41
00:02:51,230 --> 00:02:52,900
It's alright. Just eat up.

42
00:02:53,380 --> 00:02:54,350
Don't worry about it.

43
00:03:09,990 --> 00:03:12,460
Mom, this is the new induction cooker
I got you.

44
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:15,020
From now on, you should use this to cook

45
00:03:15,670 --> 00:03:16,670
instead of the stove.

46
00:03:16,950 --> 00:03:17,950
The stove is dangerous.

47
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:33,230
Mom.

48
00:03:34,140 --> 00:03:36,420
If it doesn't work out,
let's get a helper

49
00:03:37,070 --> 00:03:39,550
so that you don't have to cook anymore.

50
00:04:14,070 --> 00:04:15,070
Song Cong,

51
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:19,260
Huan'er wants to eat Aunt Hao Mei's
pork knuckles.

52
00:04:19,350 --> 00:04:20,620
She doesn't like my cooking.

53
00:04:20,820 --> 00:04:21,990
Let me learn from you, too.

54
00:04:21,990 --> 00:04:23,350
How do you make pork knuckles?

55
00:04:27,550 --> 00:04:29,710
You must teach me

56
00:04:29,710 --> 00:04:31,380
your Song family secret recipe.

57
00:04:31,820 --> 00:04:34,550
My daughter's mouth is too picky.

58
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:36,860
I've given it some thought.

59
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:39,790
I'll come to your house more for meals.

60
00:04:39,940 --> 00:04:41,500
I want to secretly steal your skills.

61
00:04:45,710 --> 00:04:46,550
Song Cong,

62
00:04:47,140 --> 00:04:48,710
buy a bouquet of flowers for Huan'er.

63
00:04:48,860 --> 00:04:51,030
Thank her for the flowers
she bought me.

64
00:04:52,380 --> 00:04:52,860
Sure.

65
00:04:53,030 --> 00:04:53,590
Go.

66
00:04:56,990 --> 00:04:58,380
Talking about these pork knuckles,

67
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:00,550
do I have to prepare
the fried sugar syrup first?

68
00:05:00,590 --> 00:05:01,990
I don't know what I am doing...

69
00:05:10,740 --> 00:05:11,790
Okay.

70
00:05:27,550 --> 00:05:28,420
Okay.

71
00:05:35,620 --> 00:05:38,180
Life goes on.

72
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:44,500
These are just hurdles to be overcome.

73
00:05:47,820 --> 00:05:49,420
It's alright.

74
00:05:50,820 --> 00:05:52,300
Stop crying.

75
00:05:52,620 --> 00:05:54,670
Hurry up and teach me how to make
pork knuckles.

76
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:57,500
Does it have to be fried in sugar syrup?

77
00:05:57,590 --> 00:05:59,910
Huan'er said that the one I made
tasted too gamey.

78
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:02,350
But I did boil it in water.

79
00:06:02,990 --> 00:06:03,990
Stop being pretentious.

80
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,400
I've been hungry for the whole day.

81
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,540
I've been waiting for these.

82
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:10,990
Hurry up. How should I make it?

83
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:15,280
It won't taste good if you make it
with an electric cooker.

84
00:06:15,300 --> 00:06:16,470
Then let's use the stove.

85
00:06:16,550 --> 00:06:18,150
We won't use the induction cooker.

86
00:06:19,260 --> 00:06:20,350
Wash it first.

87
00:06:20,420 --> 00:06:21,150
Wash it first.

88
00:06:21,230 --> 00:06:22,790
Okay, wash it first.

89
00:06:22,820 --> 00:06:23,670
Then what?

90
00:06:26,350 --> 00:06:27,620
Come on.

91
00:06:27,620 --> 00:06:28,500
Tell me quickly.

92
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:30,300
Do I need to add
onion, ginger, and garlic?

93
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:31,380
Should I marinate it?

94
00:06:31,590 --> 00:06:32,470
Yes.

95
00:06:34,420 --> 00:06:35,840
Well, I'm done washing it now...

96
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:06,220
Interested in some flowers, young lad?

97
00:07:06,420 --> 00:07:07,470
What do you want?

98
00:07:09,940 --> 00:07:11,300
(Why did you choose this flower?)

99
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:13,620
Because chamomile adapts well.

100
00:07:13,990 --> 00:07:15,590
Even in a barren environment,

101
00:07:15,590 --> 00:07:16,620
it can grow.

102
00:07:16,790 --> 00:07:17,990
Its flower language is

103
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:19,790
'never bow to fate.'

104
00:07:21,820 --> 00:07:22,590
No wonder.

105
00:07:23,940 --> 00:07:24,910
It's very much like you.

106
00:07:29,590 --> 00:07:30,590
Chamomile.

107
00:07:30,820 --> 00:07:31,300
Okay.

108
00:07:31,350 --> 00:07:32,040
How much is it?

109
00:07:32,150 --> 00:07:33,740
15 yuan, please wait a moment.

110
00:07:35,220 --> 00:07:36,150
Here are your flowers.

111
00:07:36,180 --> 00:07:36,740
Thanks.

112
00:07:48,030 --> 00:07:49,860
Run, I don't care!

113
00:07:49,860 --> 00:07:52,820
You have promised to run with me.

114
00:07:53,620 --> 00:07:56,180
I'm barely off my crutches.

115
00:07:56,230 --> 00:07:57,470
Chen Huan'er, you're too much.

116
00:07:57,470 --> 00:07:58,540
At least try it, won't you?

117
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,500
I tried. Didn't I run?

118
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:00,470
Start warming up now.

119
00:08:00,590 --> 00:08:01,590
Come, warm up with me.

120
00:08:01,710 --> 00:08:02,300
Song.

121
00:08:04,740 --> 00:08:06,350
Did you buy chamomile again?

122
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:07,910
Is it for Aunt Hao?

123
00:08:11,740 --> 00:08:12,380
Yes.

124
00:08:14,790 --> 00:08:15,910
Did Aunt Lina go today?

125
00:08:16,030 --> 00:08:16,550
Yes.

126
00:08:16,590 --> 00:08:17,300
How was it?

127
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:19,260
My mom was quite happy.

128
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:20,550
That's great.

129
00:08:21,990 --> 00:08:22,670
Huan'er.

130
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:23,990
Thank you.

131
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:26,230
Why are you thanking me?

132
00:08:26,550 --> 00:08:27,620
I'm tired of

133
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:29,230
my Mom's dishes anyway.

134
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,440
She can learn to do more.

135
00:08:30,620 --> 00:08:31,500
If you say so,

136
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:33,500
I have to get my mom to learn some too.

137
00:08:33,540 --> 00:08:35,420
Aunt Hao will have something
to do every day.

138
00:08:35,590 --> 00:08:36,310
Song Cong,

139
00:08:36,340 --> 00:08:38,860
you should spend more time with Aunt Hao
this weekend.

140
00:08:39,470 --> 00:08:40,070
Sure.

141
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:41,780
I'll go home first.

142
00:08:47,230 --> 00:08:48,260
What are you doing?

143
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:49,520
Stand up.

144
00:08:49,540 --> 00:08:50,740
- Quick.
- Let me take five.

145
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:52,420
- Get up and run with me.
- Just five minutes.

146
00:08:52,460 --> 00:08:53,950
Hurry, you promised me!

147
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:54,620
Wait a minute.

148
00:08:54,620 --> 00:08:56,150
Just five minutes. Let me take a break.

149
00:08:56,150 --> 00:08:56,900
Let me sit down.

150
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:58,470
Get up and run.

151
00:08:58,470 --> 00:08:59,190
Run.

152
00:08:59,190 --> 00:09:00,520
It hurts. It's starting to hurt.

153
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:01,190
It's aching.

154
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:02,260
Let me take five.

155
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:03,430
Just five minutes.

156
00:09:09,660 --> 00:09:10,830
The weather's nice.

157
00:09:12,230 --> 00:09:12,830
Very nice.

158
00:09:13,950 --> 00:09:15,070
At this time,

159
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:17,900
the flowers in the fields of Sishui
would be blooming.

160
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:19,180
It must be very beautiful.

161
00:09:21,110 --> 00:09:23,710
Then Sishui must be a beautiful place.

162
00:09:24,860 --> 00:09:25,830
Very beautiful.

163
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:28,380
Sishui and Tianhe are beautiful
in different ways.

164
00:09:28,950 --> 00:09:30,260
Although Sishui is remote,

165
00:09:30,350 --> 00:09:33,140
she has mountains and sea,

166
00:09:33,470 --> 00:09:35,500
and her fruits are very delicious.

167
00:09:39,470 --> 00:09:40,140
Wait...

168
00:09:42,350 --> 00:09:43,860
Have you never been to Sishui?

169
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,830
I haven't been there.

170
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:45,840
Then how did you...?

171
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:48,100
Where is Sishui?
Is it outside the country?

172
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:49,380
Sishui is a county.

173
00:09:49,780 --> 00:09:51,260
It's the westernmost county.

174
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:58,860
That happened?

175
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:00,590
Why didn't I know?

176
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:02,990
Then how did you know about Sishui?

177
00:10:03,620 --> 00:10:05,430
My mother told me that
before you came here.

178
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:08,350
She said she had a junior in college

179
00:10:08,540 --> 00:10:09,620
who was from Sishui.

180
00:10:09,620 --> 00:10:11,580
Although they weren't in contact
for a long time,

181
00:10:11,580 --> 00:10:13,900
she was getting transferred
to the family housing compound.

182
00:10:14,190 --> 00:10:15,430
She told me about their past.

183
00:10:15,430 --> 00:10:16,830
Things that happened back in school.

184
00:10:17,470 --> 00:10:18,590
She also said that Aunt Hao

185
00:10:18,590 --> 00:10:19,950
had always wanted to go to Sishui.

186
00:10:19,950 --> 00:10:22,520
But she was too busy at the hospital.
She couldn't make time to go.

187
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:23,900
Did Aunt Hao want to go to Sishui?

188
00:10:25,350 --> 00:10:27,660
We have time during the summer break.

189
00:10:27,860 --> 00:10:28,710
I can be her guide.

190
00:10:28,830 --> 00:10:30,190
She can relax over there.

191
00:10:30,260 --> 00:10:31,580
Why don't all of us go on a trip?

192
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:32,110
Sure.

193
00:10:32,860 --> 00:10:34,260
I'll go back, pack my bags,

194
00:10:34,260 --> 00:10:35,360
and tell my Mom and Dad.

195
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,830
Calm down.

196
00:10:37,350 --> 00:10:40,430
I haven't asked Song Cong and Aunt Hao.

197
00:10:41,540 --> 00:10:42,590
Just tell him

198
00:10:42,660 --> 00:10:44,350
this will help Aunt Hao to relax.

199
00:10:44,470 --> 00:10:45,640
He will definitely find a way.

200
00:10:46,830 --> 00:10:47,740
That's true.

201
00:10:48,780 --> 00:10:50,190
But what about our parents?

202
00:10:50,590 --> 00:10:51,540
Will they go?

203
00:10:51,590 --> 00:10:52,540
Don't worry about it.

204
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:53,660
I'll handle it. Let's go.

205
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:54,800
First stop, your house.

206
00:10:56,070 --> 00:10:57,260
My house? What for?

207
00:10:57,540 --> 00:10:59,660
You have to do me a small favor first.

208
00:10:59,780 --> 00:11:00,830
Then, I can guarantee

209
00:11:00,950 --> 00:11:03,470
this exclusive Sishui trip
will be a success.

210
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:06,540
So you aren't tired anymore, right?

211
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:10,540
Running is tiring, but touring isn't.
Let's go.

212
00:11:11,710 --> 00:11:13,660
Why don't we run on the way back?

213
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:14,540
You should run.

214
00:11:15,230 --> 00:11:15,740
Run with me.

215
00:11:15,740 --> 00:11:16,220
You run.

216
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,230
Run with me for a while.

217
00:11:17,230 --> 00:11:17,990
I'm not running.

218
00:11:17,990 --> 00:11:18,740
Just for a while.

219
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:20,110
I will become crippled again.

220
00:11:20,230 --> 00:11:21,640
No way. You need to recover now.

221
00:11:21,660 --> 00:11:23,080
Can we go to Sishui if I am crippled?

222
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:23,350
Come.

223
00:11:23,350 --> 00:11:23,950
Am I right?

224
00:11:24,590 --> 00:11:25,500
I'll carry you.

225
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:26,620
I'll give you a piggyback.

226
00:11:27,540 --> 00:11:29,380
What are you trying to do?

227
00:11:29,380 --> 00:11:31,380
Why are you suddenly looking
for old photos?

228
00:11:31,620 --> 00:11:32,830
Just look for them.

229
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:35,310
Make sure you're looking
for my parents' photos.

230
00:11:37,020 --> 00:11:37,620
Found it.

231
00:11:39,110 --> 00:11:39,620
Let me see.

232
00:11:48,620 --> 00:11:50,260
Is this you when you were a kid?

233
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:52,880
Why are these all pictures of you
when you were a kid?

234
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:54,460
What about your parents?

235
00:11:54,860 --> 00:11:57,020
I've only seen this album in my house.

236
00:11:58,350 --> 00:11:59,990
Forget it, I can't count on you.

237
00:12:00,110 --> 00:12:00,990
I'll get Song.

238
00:12:08,060 --> 00:12:10,500
(Speaking of this, my parents only liked
to take my photos.)

239
00:12:10,990 --> 00:12:13,020
(They never took pictures
of each other.)

240
00:12:13,540 --> 00:12:15,380
(I wonder if they never had the chance)

241
00:12:15,430 --> 00:12:17,280
(or they just don't like
being photographed.)

242
00:12:17,590 --> 00:12:19,710
(In short, their past)

243
00:12:19,950 --> 00:12:21,260
(seems to only be found)

244
00:12:21,430 --> 00:12:23,540
(in a story with me as the protagonist.)

245
00:12:35,740 --> 00:12:36,260
Is there any?

246
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:37,710
No.

247
00:12:37,740 --> 00:12:38,360
That's strange.

248
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:40,400
Your dad was still looking at it
two days ago.

249
00:12:42,710 --> 00:12:43,470
Is it this one?

250
00:12:44,020 --> 00:12:44,590
Yes.

251
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:45,660
This is the one.

252
00:12:48,990 --> 00:12:50,860
Why does Xichi want our photo album?

253
00:12:52,140 --> 00:12:53,780
He didn't tell me, either.

254
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:55,780
Tell him

255
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:57,500
if he messes around
and pisses off his Mom,

256
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:58,960
there's no one to save him this time.

257
00:12:58,960 --> 00:12:59,710
Don't worry, Mom.

258
00:12:59,900 --> 00:13:01,190
He can't do that now.

259
00:13:03,660 --> 00:13:04,230
By the way,

260
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:06,470
the work manual that Dad got

261
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:07,540
from Internal Affairs

262
00:13:07,950 --> 00:13:08,900
has many

263
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:10,380
computer system operations.

264
00:13:11,260 --> 00:13:12,620
I've made one for you.

265
00:13:13,190 --> 00:13:13,740
Look.

266
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:19,500
(Internal Affairs work manual,
computer operations)

267
00:13:19,620 --> 00:13:22,260
(Logout procedures, Login procedures)

268
00:13:25,380 --> 00:13:26,620
I'm just old.

269
00:13:27,430 --> 00:13:29,430
How will I learn
how to use the computer?

270
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:30,470
It's too much effort.

271
00:13:31,430 --> 00:13:32,860
I wasn't always like this.

272
00:13:33,350 --> 00:13:34,430
I used to learn fast.

273
00:13:34,710 --> 00:13:36,540
Any new drugs or equipment,

274
00:13:36,780 --> 00:13:38,860
I would master it in two days.

275
00:13:40,590 --> 00:13:43,020
Mom, you can still master it.

276
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:45,140
Don't worry.

277
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:46,470
You still have some time

278
00:13:46,470 --> 00:13:47,710
